<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> rdfs:label "Secondary Source: Broughton MRR II" ;
	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. II" ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Broughton, T. R. S., The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. II (99 B.C.-31 B.C.). Published by the American Philological Association. New York 1952." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Broughton MRR II" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7416> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7416" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus. With Verres in Sicily in 73 (Cic. Verr. 2.2.49), he remained with him, whether still a legate or not (see N. Marinone, AAT 100, 1965-1966, 219-252, esp. 241-246). He was a legatus in 71, and with Caesetius was in command of the fleet which captured (or found) the pirate ship (Cic. Verr. 2.5.63). See Wiseman, NM 263, no. 417.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4560> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4560" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably continued under Verres in Sicily (see 73, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4523> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4523" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Verres in Sicily (Cic. Verr. 2.2.49; see 73, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4483> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4483" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate under Lucullus in the war with Mithridates (OGIS 447; Ascon. 19 C), and a successful naval commander of the fleet of Lucullus in the Aegean and the Black Seas (App. Mith. 77; Memnon 41-43, and 48, in FGrH 3B.357-59, and 361; see above, Promagistrates, on Lucullus)." .
